news.title: Patna Civic body extends property tax deadline till February 29
news.para: If they continue to default even after February 29, their buildings and houses will specially be marked during the campaign between March 1 and 5 for further action amounting to levy of hefty fines and attachment of property.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues notices to 10,000 property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body has given the defaulters a 15-day window to clear their dues, failing to which action to confiscate the properties will be initiated.

news.title: Sebi orders attachment of bank, demat accounts of DHFL's ex-promoters in disclosure violation case
news.para: ​ Markets regulator Sebi has ordered the attachment of bank accounts as well as shares and mutual fund holdings of Dheeraj Wadhawan and Kapil Wadhawan, the former promoters of Dewan Housing Finance Corp Ltd (DHFL), to recover dues totalling over Rs 22 lakh.

news.title: SRA rehabilitation buildings’ defect liability goes up to 10 years
news.para: In a circular issued on Wednesday, SRA said revised letters of intent are to be issued mentioning the 10-year defect liability period.

news.title: Delhi: DDA auction for Phase-III of its housing scheme on March 5
news.para: DDA's Diwali Special Housing Scheme Phase III auction on March 5 offers 257 flats in Dwarka. Reserve prices range from Rs 1.44 crore to Rs 5 crore for penthouses, flats, and super HIG flats. Register online by Feb 28, pay deposit. Online auction on March 5.

news.title: PAG Asia to invest Rs 400 crore in M3M India's bonds
news.para: PAG's Asia Pragati Strategic Investment Fund will invest in Lavish Buildmart, a 100% subsidiary of M3M India the real estate developer whose promoters were questioned by the Enforcement Directorate last year for unauthorised transactions with the IREO group.

news.title: JK Cement completes acquisition of Odisha’s Toshali Cement
news.para: JK Cement has 20 million tonnes per anum of capacity and ranks amongst the top 8 cement manufacturers in the country. With the acquisition of Odisha-based Toshali Cement the company will add a further 0.6 million tonnes per anum of cement capacity.

news.title: Gurugram civic body seals tower in Ireo Gurgaon Hill as developer fails to pay tax
news.para: A team led by tax inspector Pankaj Saluja, along with tax clerks Anil and Rahul, carried out the sealing drive on Wednesday.

news.title: Delhi HC stays order on returning property seized under PMLA if no proceedings after a years’ time
news.para: The division bench was hearing an appeal filed by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) challenging the single judge's order.

news.title: NBCC to develop 13,500 new flats in five ongoing projects of Amrapali in Greater Noida
news.para: As per the direction of the Supreme Court, Amrapali Stalled Projects Investments Reconstruction Establishment (ASPIRE) was formed to complete the stuck projects of Amrapali through NBCC (India) Ltd.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP asks builders of 50 projects to file status reports
news.para: DTCP has called around 20 developers to the senior town planner (STP) office on March 1 to review the construction of these projects.

news.title: Sweden: Corem & Nyfosa's interest coverage ratios fall in Q4 2023
news.para: Shares of Nyfosa and Corem dropped 7.5% and 4% respectively in afternoon trade in Stockholm.

news.title: Spyre Proptech to raise Rs 400 crore in first phase of Rs 800-crore fund to invest in 30 startups
news.para: This fund will invest in early and growth stage startups with ticket sizes between Rs 2-8 crore in early stages and Rs 15-40 crore in growth stage series A and B rounds.

news.title: Gujarat sees housing loan uptake by 71% in Q3FY24: Report
news.para: The demand for homes in Gujarat has led to a sharp growth in home loan disbursals. The merger of HDFC and HDFC Bank has significantly contributed to the rise in housing finance disbursals.

news.title: DEO Pune starts process to take back 16 properties
news.para: Rajendra Jagtap, who took over as the defence estates officer in Jan, in a press statement said the DEO’s office has not come across any case of a sale transaction of land on which OGBs across Pune cantonment stand.

news.title: Haryana: HSVP to carve out only 17 new sectors in nine districts
news.para: Officials in HSVP admitted to the slow pace of carving out new sectors, blaming it largely to non-availability of land and the change in the pattern of acquisition.

news.title: Pune: 21 building plans under PMRDA lens over no water source
news.para: PMRDA commissioner Rahul Mahiwal said they were evaluating all the proposals and conducting checks by sending teams to the project sites to check for the water sources.

news.title: Orissa HC admits PIL against illegal registration of flat sale deeds
news.para: Bimalendu Pradhan, a resident of Bhubaneswar, filed the PIL alleging inaction of the inspector general of registration (IGR) against the illegal registration of sale deeds in projects.

news.title: HSIIDC starts e-auction of industrial plots at Panchkula
news.para: Estate manager of HSIIDC Barwala, Yogesh Kaushik, said the exercise to sell industrial plots has started. “The plots can be purchased through e-auction, which is likely to be held on March 18.

news.title: Himachal CM hails SC verdict asking Oberoi Group to vacate Wildflower Hall hotel near Shimla
news.para: Sukhu attributed the "favourable" decision to the meticulous efforts of the state government in effective pleading of the case by engaging renowned lawyer Mukul Rohatgi.
